[CLS] [SEP] ( CNN)Four workers died in a massive oil rig fire that raged for hours off the coast of Mexico Wednesday . [CLS] [SEP] Mexican state oil company Pemex said 45 workers were injured in the blaze , which began early Wednesday morning . [CLS] [SEP] Two of them are in serious condition , the company said . [CLS] [SEP] Authorities evacuated about 300 people from the Abkatun Permanente platform after the fire started , Pemex said . [CLS] [SEP] At least 10 boats worked to battle the blaze for hours . [CLS] [SEP] The fire had been extinguished by Wednesday night , Pemex said in a Twitter post . [CLS] [SEP] The company denied rumors that the platform had collapsed and said there was no oil spill as a result of the fire . [CLS] [SEP] The state oil company has n't said what caused the fire on the platform , which is located in the Gulf of Mexico 's Campeche Sound . [CLS] [SEP] The fire began in the platform 's dehydration and pumping area , Pemex said . [CLS] [SEP] CNN 's Mayra Cuevas contributed to this report .